cs.CL, cs.SI, cs.CY, cs.SD, cs.HC 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with natural language processing and machine learning for social media analytics. It may also belong to cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) as it deals with social media data and its analysis. Additionally, it may belong to cs.CY (Computers and Society) as it discusses potential biases in human learning and their impact on automated classifiers. It may also belong to cs.SD (Software Engineering) as it proposes an error-mitigating active learning algorithm. Finally, it may belong to cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) as it discusses the impact of human annotation quality on machine learning systems.
